A frontline National Chairmanship aspirant of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Senator Mohammed Sani Musa has announced his withdrawal from the race. Musa made this known in a statement issued, Saturday, by his spokesman, Nasir Mohammed. Musa, currently representing Niger East Senatorial District at the Nigerian Senate, announced this decision after the aspirantsâ€™ meeting with President Muhammadu Buhari, the leader of the party yesterday. He pledged to support Adamu, who is the choice of Buhari, to emerge as the next chairman of the party.